		<legis-type>A BILL</legis-type>
		<official-title>To require the Secretary of the Interior to convey
		  certain Federal land to Elko County, Nevada, and to take land into trust for
		  the Te-moak Tribe of Western Shoshone Indians of Nevada, and for other
		  purposes.</official-title>
	</form>
	<legis-body>
		<section id="S1" section-type="section-one">
      <enum>1.</enum>
      <header>Short
			 title; table of contents</header>
			<subsection id="idA98CF1FB1EE74D298A64B7B8B8A60118">
        <enum>(a)</enum>
        <header>Short
			 title</header>
        <text display-inline="yes-display-inline">This Act may be cited
			 as the <quote>
            <short-title>Elko Motocross and Tribal
			 Conveyance Act</short-title>
          </quote>.</text>
			</subsection>
      <subsection id="id20150CFC07B14BF68CB5B7B21FA536B6">
        <enum>(b)</enum>
        <header>Table of
			 contents</header>
        <text>The table of contents of this Act is as follows:</text>
				<toc>
					<toc-entry idref="S1" level="section">Sec. 1. Short title; table of
				contents.</toc-entry>
					<toc-entry idref="id456D190FC7CB4BF29A123F8EE6A8BFFD" level="section">Sec. 2. Definition of Secretary.</toc-entry>
					<toc-entry idref="id60C7A46165AC4572B4F4D4254FA47067" level="title">TITLE I—Elko Motocross Land Conveyance</toc-entry>
